.SH NAME
mkdir \- make a directory file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.ft B
mkdir(path, mode)
char *path;
int mode;
.fi
.ft R
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Mkdir
creates a new directory file with name
.IR path .
The mode of the new file
is initialized from
.IR mode .
(The protection part of the mode
is modified by the process's mode mask; see
.IR umask (2)).
.PP
